A 21-year-old female, believed to be a student at one of the tertiary institutions in Alice, was raped on Saturday. Provincial police spokesperson Brigadier Tembinkosi Kinana said: “There is information that the victim is a student, however we cannot confirm at this stage the institution where she is studying. Our investigation continues.” Kinana said a 48-year-old male suspect was  arrested by Alice police for allegedly raping the 21 year old female. “The two were at a house at the golf course when the incident happened,” he said. Kinana said the suspect was expected to appear before the Alice Magistrate's court on Monday, facing a charge of rape.